Q: What CSS Grid system is used in Grid Layout?
A: Bootstrap 3 Grid system.

Q: How many columns Bootstrap Grid Layout has by default?
A: 12

Q: How to define overall Grid Layout?
A:  In Data Type add Grid Layout for whole grid layout property

Q: How to restrict available editors for a row configuration?
A: Row Configuration -> Menu -> Select available editor.

Q: What are cells in row definition and how many of them you can create?
A: Cells are the definitons of layout of row definitin, what editors are available in each cell and the width of each cell. There can be a lot of cells in row definiton.

Q: Where do you create Grid layout ?
A: grid Layouts are created in Developer Section of Umbraco BackOffice.

Q: How many editors can Grid Layout cell have inside ?
A: One or more editors.

Q: How the grid is stored in database?
A: a json document with all settings and data

Q: How to render grid layout?
A: @CurrentPage.GetGridHtml("<propertyName>")

Q: How to render grid layout with diffrent renderer?
A: @CurrentPage.GetGridHtml("<propertyName>", "<nameOfCssGridFramework_eg_Bootstrap3>")

Q: Where to create the template for custom Grid layout?
A: Settings -> Partial Views -> Grid -> Create Template.

Q: Where should you put custom GridEditor?
A: In package.manifest in /App_plugins/my_folder/

Q: What wil hapend if you render grid layout property with @Umbraco.Field("gridLayoutProperty")?
A: The grid layout data json will be rendered

Q: Where do you configure Settings and Styles?
A: In the content editor

